`json\\n   144→{\\n   145→  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"Write\\\",\\n   146→  \\\"tool_input\\\": {\\\"file_path\\\": \\\"/path\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"...\\\"},\\n   147→  \\\"tool_use_id\\\": \\\"call_xxx\\\\nctc_xxx\\\"\\n   148→}\\n   149→```\\n   150→\\n   151→#### postToolUse additional fields\\n   152→\\n   153→```json\\n   154→{\\n   155→  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"Write\\\",\\n   156→  \\\"tool_input\\\": {\\\"file_path\\\": \\\"/path\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"...\\\"},\\n   157→  \\\"tool_output\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\":true}\\\",\\n   158→  \\\"duration\\\": 36.841,\\n   159→  \\\"tool_use_id\\\": \\\"call_xxx\\\\nctc_xxx\\\"\\n   160→}\\n   161→```\\n   162→\\n   163→## Transcript\\n   164→\\n   165→- Location: `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized-repo-path>/agent-transcripts/<conversation-id>.jsonl`\\n   166→  - CLI uses flat layout: `<dir>/<id>.jsonl`\\n   167→  - IDE uses nested layout: `<dir>/<id>/<id>.jsonl`\\n   168→  - The existing `ResolveSessionFile()` handles both\\n   169→- Path sanitization: leading `/` stripped, all non-alphanumeric chars replaced with `-`\\n   170→- Format: JSONL (one JSON object per line)\\n   171→- Session ID extraction: `conversation_id` field from hook payload (same value as `session_id`)\\n   172→- Example entries:\\n   173→\\n   174→```jsonl\\n   175→{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"<user_query>\\\\ncreate a file\\\\n</user_query>\\\"}]}}\\n   176→{\\\"role\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Created the file.\\\"}]}}\\n   177→```\\n   178→\\n   179→- Note: Transcript does NOT contain tool_use blocks — file detection relies on git status\\n   180→- Override for testing: set `ENTIRE_TEST_CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR` env var to override the transcript directory\\n   181→\\n   182→## Config Preservation\\n   183→\\n   184→- `.cursor/hooks.json`: Read-modify-write using `map[string]json.RawMessage` to preserve unknown fields\\n   185→- `~/.cursor/cli-config.json`: User-level config — do not modify (contains auth, permissions, model settings)\\n   186→- Keys to preserve: `version`, any unknown hook types, user's custom hooks\\n   187→\\n   188→## CLI Flags\\n   189→\\n   190→- Non-interactive prompt: `agent -p \\\"prompt text\\\" --force --trust --workspace <dir>`\\n   191→  - `-p` / `--print`: Headless mode, prints response to stdout\\n   192→  - `--force` / `--yolo`: Auto-approve all tool use\\n   193→  - `--trust`: Trust workspace without prompting (headless only)\\n   194→  - `--workspace <path>`: Set working directory\\n   195→  - `--model <model>`: Model override (e.g., `sonnet-4`, `gpt-5`)\\n   196→  - `--output-format <fmt>`: `text` (default), `json`, `stream-json`\\n   197→- Interactive mode: `agent --force` (launches TUI)\\n   198→  - Prompt pattern for TUI ready: TBD (needs interactive probe)\\n   199→  - `--resume [chatId]`: Resume specific session\\n   200→  - `--continue`: Resume most recent session\\n   201→- Relevant env vars:\\n   202→  - `CURSOR_API_KEY`: API key for authentication\\n   203→  - `ENTIRE_TEST_CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR`: Override transcript directory (for testing)\\n   204→  - `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0`: Disable TTY detection in Entire hooks\\n   205→\\n   206→## Gaps & Limitations\\n   207→\\n   208→1. **`beforeSubmitPrompt` and `stop` don't fire in `-p` mode**: This is the main limitation. In headless mode, Entire won't get TurnStart/TurnEnd events. Checkpoints can only be created via sessionStart/sessionEnd flow. E2E tests using `RunPrompt` won't trigger the normal TurnStart→TurnEnd checkpoint flow.\\n   209→2. **`transcript_path` is always `null` in CLI mode**: Handled by existing `resolveTranscriptRef()` which computes the path dynamically.\\n   210→3. **No `composer_mode` field in CLI**: IDE sends `\\\"agent\\\"`, CLI omits it. Not impactful.\\n   211→4. **Transcript lacks tool_use blocks**: Modified file detection relies on git status (already handled).\\n   212→5. **`tool_use_id` format**: Contains newline (`call_xxx\\\\nctc_xxx`) — may need sanitization if used as identifiers.\\n   213→\\n   214→## Captured Payloads\\n   215→\\n   216→Probe run on 2026-03-02 using `agent -p` in a temp git repo.\\n   217→\\n   218→Hooks captured in headless (`-p`) mode:\\n   219→- `sessionStart` (1 capture)\\n   220→- `sessionEnd` (1 capture)\\n   221→- `preToolUse` (2 captures: Read, Write)\\n   222→- `postToolUse` (1 capture: Write)\\n   223→\\n   224→Hooks NOT captured in headless mode:\\n   225→- `beforeSubmitPrompt` — does not fire in `-p` mode\\n   226→- `stop` — does not fire in `-p` mode\\n   227→- `preCompact` — requires long context (not triggered by short prompt)\\n   228→- `subagentStart/Stop` — requires subagent usage\\n   229→\\n   230→See `.entire/tmp/probe-cursor-cli-*/captures/` for raw JSON captures.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"e97988bd-4b22-4a96-869d-2037138a8b5e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T16:48:55.856Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a0cc04a1d8cf42c82\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01AD2VbAv4v4r5bHT6GTYic4\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_013sHKyk5zqwZAkunmnNx4eK\",\"uuid\":\"4dfa6a0d-e287-4145-b59e-976a72deac46\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T16:48:56.026Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4dfa6a0d-e287-4145-b59e-976a72deac46\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"f9e370ac-2e48-4464-9976-3c8789894fec\",\"version\":\"2.1.68\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"majestic-swinging-kernighan\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T16:49:01.017Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Q2WrCPW5RPSqccFDaD7mEh\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01VaYqwAXA4vNVF1PQGKV2p6\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire-agent-test/main.go\"